# ExplainNet Environment Variables

## Required Variables

### YouTube API
YOUTUBE_API_KEY=your_youtube_api_key_here

### Gemini API (Primary - for YouTube analysis)
# Used for: video transcripts, comments sentiment, entity extraction
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_primary_gemini_api_key_here

### Gemini API (Secondary - for News articles) - OPTIONAL
# If you have a second Gemini API account, you can use it for news article summaries
# This helps avoid rate limits by splitting the load across two accounts
# If not set, will use GEMINI_API_KEY for both YouTube and News
GEMINI_API_KEY_NEWS=your_secondary_gemini_api_key_here

### HuggingFace API - OPTIONAL
# If not set, HuggingFace will use free tier with rate limits
# Local transformers fallback will be used if API fails
HUGGINGFACE_API_KEY=your_huggingface_api_key_here

### CORS Origins
# Comma-separated list of allowed frontend origins
ALLOW_ORIGINS=http://localhost:4200,http://127.0.0.1:4200

### Guardian News API
GUARDIAN_API_KEY=your_guardian_api_key_here

### NewsAPI
NEWS_API_KEY=your_newsapi_key_here

## How to Use Dual Gemini API Keys

1. Create two Google Cloud accounts (or use two different Google accounts)
2. Get a Gemini API key from each account at https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey
3. Set GEMINI_API_KEY to your first account's key (used for YouTube)
4. Set GEMINI_API_KEY_NEWS to your second account's key (used for News)

This doubles your rate limit: each account gets 10 requests/minute free tier, so you get:
- 10/min for YouTube analysis (transcripts + comments)
- 10/min for News article summaries

## Rate Limits (Free Tier)

- Gemini: 10 requests per minute per API key
- HuggingFace: Limited requests without API key
- YouTube: 10,000 quota units per day (varies by operation)
- Guardian: 500 requests per day
- NewsAPI: 100 requests per day (free tier)
